// FRONTIER REPRO — currently RED. Pins a Koru COMPILER bug, not a library bug.
//
// A phantom obligation minted in an imported module (`Cursor<live!>` from
// libs/yaml) is rejected when it flows through a `#loop` / `@loop` BACK-EDGE,
// with a namespace-qualification mismatch:
//
//   error[KORU030]: Phantom state mismatch: expected 'index:live'
//                   but got 'libs.yaml:live!' for argument 'c2'
//
// `index:` is libs/yaml/index.kz's own module name; `libs.yaml:` is the import
// alias the obligation is minted under. Straight-line threading of the SAME
// obligation normalizes these correctly (yaml/tests/walk.kz and scalars.kz walk
// the cursor through repeated `advance` calls and pass). Only the back-edge
// re-resolution drops the import-alias normalization.
//
// This is NOT "held-across" specific: here `c2` is the loop's own threaded
// variable — consumed by `advance` and freshly re-minted every turn — not a
// value carried across an unrelated fold. The mismatch is purely: obligation
// minted under an import alias + `@loop` edge. In a SAME-FILE loop the two
// module names coincide, so the mismatch cannot arise (cf. koru
// tests/regression/.../330_085_obligation_held_across_back_edge, which is
// same-file and green).
//
// Reproduce:
//   koruc run yaml/tests/frontier/loop_crossmodule_backedge.kz
//   -> error[KORU030]: Phantom state mismatch: expected 'index:live'
//                      but got 'libs.yaml:live!' for argument 'c2'
//
// When fixed upstream, this goes green and the unbounded streaming walk (see the
// commented loop in index.kz's header) becomes the headline example.

~import libs/yaml
~import std/io

~libs/yaml:open(input: "a: 1")
| ok p |> libs/yaml:begin(parser: p)
    | at c |> #loop libs/yaml:advance(cur: c)
        | at c2 |> @loop(c2)
        | eof pp |> libs/yaml:close(parser: pp) |> std/io:print.ln("done")
        | err ep |> libs/yaml:close(parser: ep) |> std/io:print.ln("parse error")
    | eof pp0 |> libs/yaml:close(parser: pp0) |> std/io:print.ln("empty")
    | err ep0 |> libs/yaml:close(parser: ep0) |> std/io:print.ln("parse error at start")
| err e |> std/io:print.ln("open error: {{ e:s }}")
